review_blob: not alot going on with this beer unfortunately but maybe it was how it travelled to singapore. light colour aroma lacking, probably good on a hot day to quench the thirst but not with a meal for me.
A very refreshing beer perfect for a session in the tropics, some very nice flavour coming through and a fresh crisp finish. A hint of citrus and tropical fruit coming through. very well balanced
beer_name: Barrabool Hills Cockies Surf Coast Blonde

review_blob: quite an easy drink especially in the singapore heat but not enough flavour for my palete. The appearance was alittle murky. An ok beer but needs some work on the depth of flavour.

some very nice grapefruit flavour coming through and some other citrus, very nice on the nose and the finish very smooth given what is quite a big pale ale. The colour is very nice and golden and crystal clear. From that part of the world I have tried the Little Creatures Pale Ale and I much prefer this one. A bit bigger but has a smoother finish.
beer_name: Barrabool Hills Cockies Ocean Road Pale Ale
